    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>HTTPS Concept Demo</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 2rem;\n    background-color: #f0f4fc;\n    color: #111;\n  }\n  header {\n    text-align: center;\n    margin-bottom: 2rem;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    color: #0069d9;\n  }\n  section {\n    background: white;\n    padding: 1.5rem;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n    max-width: 600px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n  }\n  .lock-icon {\n    display: inline-block;\n    vertical-align: middle;\n    margin-right: 0.5rem;\n  }\n  svg {\n    fill: #28a745;\n    width: 24px;\n    height: 24px;\n  }\n  button {\n    background-color: #0069d9;\n    border: none;\n    color: white;\n    padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n  }\n  button:disabled {\n    background-color: #bbb;\n    cursor: not-allowed;\n  }\n  #message {\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n    background-color: #eaf5ea;\n    border: 1px solid #c3e6cb;\n    color: #155724;\n    padding: 0.8rem;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    display: none;\n  }\n  .explanation {\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    line-height: 1.4;\n    color: #444;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<header>\n  <h1><span class=\"lock-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M12 2C9.243 2 7 4.243 7 7v3H6c-1.103 0-2 .897-2 2v7c0 1.104.897 2 2 2h12c1.103 0 2-.896 2-2v-7c0-1.103-.897-2-2-2h-1V7c0-2.757-2.243-5-5-5zm-3 8V7c0-1.654 1.346-3 3-3s3 1.346 3 3v3h-6zm5 2v5h-4v-5h4z\"/></svg>\n  </span> HTTPS Demo</h1>\n</header>\n<section>\n  <p>\n    HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) is the secure version of HTTP — the protocol over which data is sent between your browser and the website you're connected to. The 'S' at the end of HTTPS stands for 'Secure' and it means all communications between your browser and the website are encrypted.\n  </p>\n\n  <button id=\"simulateBtn\">Simulate HTTPS Handshake</button>\n  <div id=\"message\"></div>\n\n  <div class=\"explanation\">\n    <h3>What happens during an HTTPS connection?</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All data sent and received is encrypted, preventing eavesdropping.</li>\n      <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> The website presents a trusted certificate proving its identity.</li>\n      <li><strong>Integrity:</strong> Data cannot be modified in transit without being detected.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>This simulation will show a simplified HTTPS handshake process where your browser and a server establish a secure connection.</p>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n  const btn = document.querySelector(\"#simulateBtn\");\n  const msg = document.querySelector(\"#message\");\n\n  // Simulate steps of a simplified HTTPS handshake\n  const steps = [\n    { text: \"Browser: Initiates a secure connection (ClientHello)\", delay: 1500 },\n    { text: \"Server: Responds with a digital certificate and ServerHello\", delay: 2000 },\n    { text: \"Browser: Validates the server certificate's authenticity\", delay: 1800 },\n    { text: \"Browser: Generates a session key and encrypts it using server's public key\", delay: 2000 },\n    { text: \"Server: Decrypts the session key with its private key\", delay: 1800 },\n    { text: \"Both: Secure communication channel established with symmetric encryption\", delay: 1500 }\n  ];\n\n  async function simulateHttpsHandshake() {\n    btn.disabled = true;\n    msg.style.display = \"block\";\n    msg.textContent = \"Starting HTTPS handshake...\";\n    \n    for (let i = 0; i < steps.length; i++) {\n      await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, steps[i].delay));\n      msg.textContent = steps[i].text;\n    }\n\n    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 2000));\n    msg.textContent = \"🔐 Secure HTTPS connection established! All data is now encrypted.\";\n    btn.disabled = false;\n  }\n\n  btn.addEventListener(\"click\", simulateHttpsHandshake);\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
